China’s Sina Falls the Most in Eight Days in New York Trading

-- B y   B e l i n d a   C a o
-- 
2011-07-21T16:25:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/china-s-sina-falls-the-most-in-eight-days-in-new-york-trading.html
Sina Corp., the owner of  China ’s
third-most visited website and the Twitter-like Weibo service,
fell the most in eight days in New York Trading.  Sina declined 4.9 percent to $113.22 at 12:13 p.m. New York
time, the biggest intraday loss since July 11. It earlier
slumped as much as 7.3 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Belinda Cao in New York at 
 lcao4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  